xxl.core.io.converters

Class MultiConverter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.io.converters.Converter<T>
      • xxl.core.io.converters.MultiConverter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to be converted.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class MultiConverter<T>
extends Converter<T>
    Converts an object with multiple convertable fields into a byte representation and vice versa.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Field Detail

      • converters

        protected Converter<Object>[] converters
        The converters that is wrapped. The converter must be able to read and write uniform objects.

      • createObject

        protected Function<Object,? extends T> createObject
        A factory method that is used for creating the object to be read. This function will be invoked when the read method is called (even if there is an object specified to restore).

      • objectToObjectArray

        protected Function<? super T,Object[]> objectToObjectArray
        A function which converts the components of the object into an array of objects.

    • Method Detail

      • read

        public T read(DataInput dataInput,
              T object)
       throws IOException
        Reads the state (the attributes) for the specified object from the specified data input and returns the restored object.

        This implementation calls the read method of the wrapped converter. When the specified object is null it is initialized by invoking the function (factory method).

        Specified by:
        read in class Converter<T>
        Parameters:
        dataInput - the stream to read data from in order to restore the object.
        object - the object to be restored. If the object is null it is initialized by invoking the function (factory method).
        Returns:
        the restored object.
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O errors occur.

      • write

        public void write(DataOutput dataOutput,
                  T object)
           throws IOException
        Writes the state (the attributes) of the specified object to the specified data output.

        This implementation calls the write method of the wrapped converter.

        Specified by:
        write in class Converter<T>
        Parameters:
        dataOutput - the stream to write the state (the attributes) of the object to.
        object - the object whose state (attributes) should be written to the data output.
